	<li>Bill to collect (Revenue and Receivables)</li>
	<li>Treasury</li>
	<li>Taxation</li>
	<li>Deposits</li>
	<li>Derivatives</li>
</ul>

<p>Preparation of a RCM is nothing but the documentation method for the Internal Control Framework and help in reporting on the working efficiency of Internal Financial Controls.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p>The significant part is to understand the interaction between the business cycles and the related activities or processes and the account balances affecting the same, to the degree it affects the financial reporting. Finally, the RCM also assists to recognize controls which are relevant and not relevant.</p>

